column5: Nice day on the water and better results then last weekend. Went out with couple friends east of the ferry. This week we fished in 140FOW down 50ft. We caught 3 nice walleye and 2 golden bass if you know what I mean guys Here are some pics: I would like to thank Sam at Carra's in Belliville for setting me up with a nice Okuma rod and reel. Well worth the trip to your store.
congrats nice looking walleyes you got there  rob
Nice bay of quinte walleyes !!!!!! well done,cheers
Nice bay of quinte walleyes !!!!!!!....well done, cheers
Nice report and pics!  Looks like they were keepers eh!
Nice fish and good report.  We've got the best Trophy Walleye Fishing in NA.

Yes They were keepers. I dont keep to much from boq but if someone from my boat want to keep fish I dont have a problem with that. Maybe next time I will take you out fishing so you can have some BOQ walleye
